\b Possible words from letter lists Search (meta search) : choosing words that fit based on the crossing words.\b0\par
\par
A routine that takes a list of possible letters (based on all the crossing word masks) for each position in a word. \par
It's output is a list of words that can be made with said letters.\par
@words = &WordsFromLetterLists(['C','D','F','T','Z'] , ['E','R','T','Y','O'] , ['T','R','E','W','Q','Z']);\par
Used if we check all possible letters at the same word position of crossing words. Then we can find the possible perpendicular words that are possible for this spot\par
Obviously it takes a lot of processing time as we are searching multiple lists of words for words common to all the lists.\par
